<HEADER>
A9685 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r a BC-FAUCET-ART-LADN     09-12 0335
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FAUCET-ART-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PFIRST PLACE PFINISH
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROBERT MONROE 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ This was no contest for drips.
</P>
<P>
   A student at Pasadena's Art Center College of Design is the
winner of Price Pfister's first-ever Pfaucet of the Pfuture
contest, the Pacoima-based company said Monday. Winner Silas Beebe
gets $10,000 and a boost to a career going anywhere but down the
drain. Price Pfister gets to keep all 30 faucet designs in the
competition as its own.
</P>
<P>
   ``The students did a good job of recognizing what is needed out
in the marketplace,'' said Price Pfister President Les Ireland.
``They thought about style but they also thought about
functionality.''
</P>
<P>
   Beebe's winning design, called ``Water Go,'' is a looping
bathtub faucet that encloses a bath caddy on which a bar of soap, a
candle, a razor or other items can be placed.
</P>
<P>
   ``I tried to incorporate functions like a bath caddy and make
the faucet do something other than just pour water,'' said Beebe, a
27-year-old transplant from Portland, Ore.
</P>
<P>
   Other top entries featured a faucet without handles that turned
on simply with a push upward and one named ``Chameleon'' in which a
temperature-sensitive film shows the user how hot or cold the water
is by changing color.
</P>
<P>
   Beebe said he had already designed the faucet for his product
design class, so entering it in the contest was easy. He gets a
$5,000 scholarship and his school gets an additional $5,000 for his
victory. He said his horoscope told him he was going to win a
contest the day he submitted the entry.
</P>
<P>
   Despite his bathroom fixture conquest, Beebe said he wants to
get into other kinds of design consulting such as automotive
design.
</P>
<P>
   ``Hopefully this success will translate to other things,'' he
said.
</P>
<P>
   Of the 30 designs entered, visitors to Price Pfister's Web site
narrowed the list down to 10. A panel of industrial design experts
then picked the winners.
</P>
<P>
   XXX
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-09-12-00 0021EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
