<HEADLINE>
PITCHING DIRECTION UNDER DISCUSSION
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JOE HAAKENSON  
 c.2000 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ANAHEIM _ The pitching coaches from throughout the Anaheim
Angels organization will meet today to discuss the club's direction
with its pitchers.
</P>
<P>
   One of the topics on the agenda will concern injuries -- how to
prevent them and why so many of their younger pitchers have come
down with arm, shoulder and even rib cage injuries recently.
</P>
<P>
   The Angels understand a Tim Belcher or Ken Hill are going to
have health issues, but this year has seen injuries to their future
-- Ramon Ortiz, Seth Etherton, Jarrod Washburn, Jason Dickson,
Scott Schoeneweis and Matt Wise.
</P>
<P>
   ''We're going to look at everything happening within the
organization,'' manager Mike Scioscia said. ''Our philosophy of
pitch counts, to the mechanics we're teaching, to the medical end
of it. I'd be surprised if we can narrow it down to one thing. I
think it's a combinations of things. It's one of the things
(general manager) Bill Stoneman has on his plate this winter.
</P>
<P>
   ''It's no secret the key to a championship-caliber club is the
health of the pitching staff.''
</P>
<P>
   The pitching coaches in the organization are: Bud Black (major
league level), Greg Minton (Triple-A Edmonton), Howie Gershberg
(Double-A Erie), Kernan Ronan (Single-A Lake Elsinore), Randy
Kramer (Single-A Cedar Rapids), Zeke Zimmerman (short season
Single-A Boise) and Mike Butcher (Rookie League Butte).
</P>
<P>
   Pitcher Scott Karl will be skipped in the starting rotation this
week, replaced by reliever Al Levine, who will start Friday in
Minnesota.
</P>
<P>
   Karl is 0-2 with a 9.53 in three starts since signing with the
club three weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
   ''I think we're at the point where Scott needs the oppurtunity
to pitch,'' Scioscia said. ''But it's a catch-22 because we can't
afford that luxury at this point in the season. We're looking for
productive starts right now, and Scott has had a problem getting
his feet on the ground.''
</P>
<P>
   Washburn (four innings) and Etherton (three innings) each threw
a simulated game and reported feeling good. However, neither one
will pitch in another game this season.
</P>
<P>
   Washburn has a stress fracture in his left shoulder and Etherton
has tendinitis in his right shoulder.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
