 ART ADV.: Photos with MEDSCHOOL-RACE, CONCORD-REVIEW,
MANAGING-MONEY, MFS-OUTLOOK and TV-SPORTS-COLUMN are being
transmitted to NYT Photo Service subscribers.  
 For Immediate Release  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Boston Globe plans to move the following FEATURE stories for
use by NYTimes News Service clients.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; For questions about stories, please contact  &UR; Frank Perrotta
 &LR; at the Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;  For individual purchase of
budgeted graphics or photos please call  &UR; 888-346-9867  &LR; or
 &UR; 888-603-1036 &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CANADA-INDIANS (Montreal) _ Legal actions _ brought by Indians
who claim their heritage and language were stolen in church-run
schools _ is bankrupting the Anglicans and causing deep financial
woes to the three other major Christian churches in Canada. By
Colin Nickerson. 1180 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   MEDSCHOOLS-RACE (Undated) _ Anyone whose parents immigrated from
the Dominican Republic, Haiti, Jamaica, South and Central America,
and the whole continent of Africa can't apply to most medical
schools under affirmative action programs. By Cindy Rodriguez. 1270
words. PHOTO
</P>
<P>
   EX-GAYS (Undated) _ For years, Mark Pierpont took his message
around the world. Now, though, he's part of the burgeoning backlash
-- they call themselves the ``ex-ex-gays.'' By Tatsha Robertson.
1380 words.
</P>
<P>
   EARLY-SALOON (Virginia City, Nev.) _ The excavation of the
Boston Saloon, run by a Massachusetts native, provides an insight
into the life of free blacks in the 19th century. By Lynda Gorov.
1190 words.
</P>
<P>
   CONCORD-REVIEW (Sudbury, Mass.) _ To Will Fitzhugh, it seemed
like an inoffensive idea: publish the best history essays by high
school students around the country. But, 13 years later, the
Concord Review is still a controversial venture. By Marcella
Bombardieri. 1340 words. PHOTO
</P>
