</P>
<P>
   SCI-VENTS (Undated) _ Violent and unearthly places known as
hydrothermal vents may have a surprisingly nurturing side. These
ocean hotspots may have been the cradle in which life began. By
David L. Chandler. 1680 words.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-PLASTIC (Undated) _ Americans are turning to plastic
surgeons in record numbers, fueling more than a doubling of breast
enhancements, tummy tucks and liposuctions since 1992. But even
plastic surgeons say the industry needs to say ``no'' more often.
By Anne Barnard. 1500 words.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-LOONS (Undated) _ In its most extensive findings to date, a
research team says New England loons are dying from mercury
contamination, with reproduction rates down 50 percent. By Robert
Braile. 850 words.
</P>
<P>
