</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ Thank you, Gloria Steinem. The
feminist pioneer who helped women move into the economic, political
and legal mainstream of our male-dominated culture has done it
again. Once dead set against marriage, calling it a form of
imprisonment, Steinem has gotten married herself now that she is a
senior citizen. She is demonstrating that age need not be a barrier
to wedded bliss, a psychological breakthrough as important in its
way as the independence she has always preached. By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
<P>
   HINES-COLUMN (Washington) _ The Republican's circular firing
squad has stood down, but it could regroup on a moment's notice.
About this time last week, veteran Republican whingers knew that
several new national polls were about to hit. They thought George
W. Bush was in for more bad numbers so they elbowed to the front of
the line to get in their usually anonymous licks early against
their beleaguered candidate. By CRAGG HINES.
</P>
<P>
   ELY-COLUMN (Houston) _ George W. Bush has let Al Gore trick him
into running on details over which the president has little or no
control. Bush _ and the electorate _ need to remember that he and
Gore are running for president and not the Congress. By JANE ELY.
</P>
</TEXT>
