<P>
   Online course tackles sports violence
</P>
<P>
   Yahoo to assist NBA, WNBA marketing
</P>
<P>
   SAVE TIME ONLINE: All stories and urls in this column are one
click away on ajc.com/enews
</P>
<P>
   POSITIVE COURSE: Violence at youth sports events, such as former
Texas Rangers outfielder Pete Incaviglia's recent run-in at his
son's hockey game, is a national problem. Stanford University
offers an online solution with its Positive Coaching Alliance, an
initiative to teach organizers, coaches and parents new techniques
for violence prevention. The Positive Coaching Alliance Workshop
was developed in partnership with the Boston-based Knowledge
Marketing company, LearningBrands. The course, offered at no
charge, aims to combat the ``win-at-all-cost'' mentality by
developing leadership and management skills.
</P>
<P>
   www.positivecoach.org
</P>
<P>
   HOOP DREAMS: Yahoo! Inc. has announced a marketing partnership
with the NBA and WNBA. The site will provide daily video
highlights, real-time game statistics, and live game and press
conference telecasts. Yahoo also will host auctions and an online
mall.
</P>
