Angeles County's fourth quarter 1999 were up 12.1 percent over
1998. This is the biggest gain since 1986, when they first started
keeping the data. Statewide numbers called it ``stunning.'' Car
dealers and building materials led the pack. By Pam Park. (Will
also move on the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news wires.)
