<P>
   PREDATOR (Phoenix) - The Arizona Game and Fish Commission's
proposal to ban predator hunting contests got shot, skinned, gutted
and thrown out by a state panel Tuesday. There is no chance of
resurrection. The Governor's Regulatory Review Council not only
threw out the proposed ban on contests where hunters compete to see
who can kill the most nuisance creatures in a set amount of time,
it also questioned whether the Game and Fish commissioners had the
legal authority to manage wildlife in the state. By the time the
meeting was over, the bill's blood was filling the scuppers of the
speaker's well, and the Game and Fish employees were shaking their
heads, wondering what it all meant. By JUDD SLIVKA. Story will move
in the ``A'' category.
</P>
