<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-E-LIVING13-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    E-living column
 &HT;    By John Druckenmiller
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QR;  e-Holster lets you keep the Internet in your armpit
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Shuttle launch tickets enter (cyber)space
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Wormwood'' author posting each chapter as written
</P>
<P>
   UNDERCOVER: It's high noon and your flight's been canceled. OK
Air might have a few seats _ but it's going to be a shootout. You
reach into that holster under your coat and _ bam! _ out comes the
PDA to check flight plans. Bam! Out comes the cellphone to make
reservations. Bam! Out comes the e-book because you'll have some
time to kill before the new flight. Holster? Make that e-Holster,
new from Personal Electronics Concealment. The over-the-shoulder,
under-the-arm accessory keeps gadgets close _ though you risk a
techno-geek reputation if you've got no jacket on (think ultimate
pocket protector). It conceals your valuables in two or three
Velcro-closure compartments. Cost: $99.95 in leather; $41.95 for
the neoprene version.
</P>
<P>
   www.eholster.com
</P>
<P>
   SHUTTLE TICKETS: Does today's ``Destination Mir'' story about a
space-themed ``Survivor'' on Page E1 leave you eager to visit the
final frontier? How about viewing a shuttle launch? You can order
tickets to shuttle launches online; prices range from $15 to $34.50
for seats six miles from the action (front row when compared with
other areas). Remember: Few of the nearly 100 launches to date have
gone off as scheduled (think Hartsfield on a busy, or even slow,
day). If the mission is delayed or scrubbed before you get to the
viewing area, you can come back for the next attempt. But if the
mission is delayed after you get to the viewing area, you're out of
luck. The next scheduled launches are Oct. 5 and Nov. 30. All 5,000
tickets for the most recent launch were sold, with a Swiss couple
the first online Aug. 15.
</P>
<P>
   www.kennedyspacecenter.com
</P>
<P>
   ONLINE ONSLAUGHT? Author Fay Weldon is following Stephen King's
virtual footsteps with her new book, ``Wormwood or Love Amongst the
Scientists.'' The author of ``The Lives and Loves of a She-Devil''
and other titles, Weldon is serializing ``Wormwood'' online. You
can go to the site below to get episode one, titled ``Before the
Prize.'' Chapter two will be posted as soon as it is written. Even
better: There's a feedback button where fans _ or critics _ can
send comments to the author.
</P>
<P>
   www.yougov.com
</P>
<P>
   SEARCH ENGINE:
</P>
<P>
   SITES
</P>
<P>
   Service tells you where to call should nature call
</P>
<P>
   Here's a must for the upcoming holiday travel or for any road
trip. Take eXitSource, which provides real-time information on all
businesses and services at every U.S. interstate exit via your
mobile web phone mobile. Get instant information about restaurants,
hotels, gas stations, pharmacies, ATMs, etc. by entering your state
and exit number. There's even a hot button for instant information
on medical facilities. The free service is available on Nextel and
Verizon phones, or can be found by by typing in the numerical
address 216.205.12.122. Directories and CD-ROMs are available for
purchase. For those who prefer to pre-plan, try:
</P>
<P>
   www.exitsource.com
</P>
<P>
   Every day's a holiday if you have the right calendar
</P>
<P>
   One more travel note: You're ready for that two-week tour of
Ireland but want to take in a little more color and culture than
some other travelers. So where do you check before booking the
flight? Try the Earth Calendar, where every day is a holiday.
Included: Holidays and cultural celebrations around the world. (As
for Ireland: Oct. 23 is the October Holiday, so hoist a pint!)
</P>
<P>
   www.earthcalendar.net
</P>
<P>
   Virtual one-stop service for changing your address
</P>
<P>
   Speaking of traveling, if you're on the move _ presumably for
good _ check out this site. It lets change your address via a few
simple steps (among them paying $9.95 for the service). Banks,
frequent flyer programs, magazines and others will be notified of
your relocation, and you can start looking forward to the junk mail
again!
</P>
<P>
   www.changeaddress.com
</P>
<P>
   EVENTS
</P>
<P>
   IT'S AUCTION MAN! Consider it the ultimate garage sale, only the
booty comes from the cavernous Batcave and not the haunting
two-vehicle menace just outside your kitchen door. Warner Brothers
is selling costumes, props and memorabilia from the last three
``Batman'' movies. Up for grabs: Goodies such as Batman's cowl from
``Batman Forever,'' Catwoman's costume from ``Batman Returns,'' The
Riddler and Two Face costumes from ``Batman Forever'' and other
unnamed items. All come with a certificate of authenticity, which
is a good thing. Who would believe it, otherwise?
</P>
<P>
   www.warnerbrosauction.com
</P>
<P>
   CYPRESS LINK: Cypress Hill has made it to the top of the rap
ranks solely on the strength of their music; all of their albums
have gone gold or platinum even without radio singles.
</P>
<P>
   7 tonight at chat.msn.com
