SAN FRANCISCO _  FOOD INTRO  _ This week's special Food issue is
devoted to helping Bay Area cooks find their way around the brave
new world of cyberspace that blends food and technology. Using the
Internet is a lot like cooking _ if you don't have good equipment,
both pursuits can become difficult. 
 By Kim Severson  
 c. 2000 The San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
SAN FRANCISCO _  &UR; NET FOOD &LR;  _ Although the Internet has promised to
revolutionize how we live, many of those promises have yet to
materialize in the kitchen. Online grocery shopping sales remain
flat, cooking Web sites battle to be recognized and diners and
restaurateurs still rely on the telephone to handle reservations.
How long will it be until the Internet invades America's stomach?
Experts are divided. &QL; 
 &UR; By Kim Severson &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; c. 2000 The San Francisco Chronicle &QL;  &LR; 
