<SLUG> BC-BUSINESS-TRAVEL-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
AS COSTS SOAR, BUSINESS TRAVEL DEPARTMENTS REVISE POLICIES 
</HEADLINE>
   (duplication notice: also sent with `f' code)  
 By JOE SHARKEY  
 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``Lately, dealing with my corporate travel department is like
being pecked to death by a duck,'' said a senior executive I know
who travels more than 100,000 miles a year on business and feels
that he is being increasingly second-guessed by the bean counters
