such costs were first tracked. World-wide, about $396 billion is
spent annually on business travel, according to Marianne McInerney,
the executive director of the National Business Travel Association.
</P>
<P>
   The American Express survey, Trends and Forecasts for the
Business Travel Industry: Preview 2001, estimates that business air
fares, hotel rates and car rentals are all expected to rise by at
least 5 percent next year.
</P>
<P>
   Business air fares, which American Express said rose 8 percent
in the second quarter compared with the same period last year, are
