government's support network when a loved one is dying. Dee
Harmeling, left, and her granddaughter Jennifer Arnold, 15, are
thankful for the Hospice of Dayton. When Harmeling's daughter
Sandra Lee Hughes, Jennifer's mother, was dying from cancer,
Hospice of Dayton not only took over Hughes' care -- and did not
charge the family a penny -- but the care of her family as well,
making sure there were enough medical supplies and food in the
house. (Lisa Powell/Cox News Service Photo)
