famed red swirl logo symbolized its lifeblood going down the drain.
But the world's largest telecommunications company is fighting its
way back, jettisoning its slow-growing office network installation
business and taking other steps to sharpen its focus on advanced
communications gear, especially optical devices. Brent
Searle-Spratt works on a Lambda Router at Lucent which contains
tiny mirrored devices that redirect Internet traffic from one
fiber-optic strand to another. (John Blanding/The Boston Globe)
